@node "Adminwords" "The word(s) from the administrator for this edition"

@{b}->  The word(s) from the administrator for this edition@{ub}

@{b}@{fg shine}o@{fg text}@{ub}   This edition appears very, very late. There just was no other
    way around. I'll keep these delays to a minimum, but I don't give any
    garantees. Let's see what happens to the next HoF :-)

@{b}@{fg shine}o@{fg text}@{ub}   If everything went well, this edition should have been accompanied
    by the @{i}HoF scoring utility@{ui} which Grant Reeve wrote and which I use to 
    calculate the scores and ranking. It was only sent to members via E-Mail,
    so don't expect to find it on UseNet or the F1GP Homepages.
    Using the program isn't very complicated, so find out about it yourself :)
    At least now you can see what your own records are worth _before_ the HoF
    actually gets released.

@{b}@{fg shine}o@{fg text}@{ub}   As a general reminder: please swap to the latest version of any
    utility, just to make sure you are complying with the rules. If possible,
    new releases are announced here, but to be really certain you could always
    visit the F1GP homepages or Aminet's game/misc directory.

    @{b}In addition to this, Oliver has just released version 3.10. There
    have been some changes in layout _and_ function. The rules for the HoF
    should be updated to reflect this, but are still leaping behind.
    I assume most of you can make a correct 'translation' from old to new
    rules...Oliver already sent me the changes, which I should fit in sometime
    F1GP-Ed v3.10 can be found in the 'recent' dir too now, but will move on
    to its normal location, game/misc.@{ub}

@endnode

