@node "WhatIs" "What this Hall of Fame is...or should be"

@{b}->  A short introduction@{ub}

If you flipped to this page, then you probably are new to this Hall of Fame.
So some sort of introduction would be in place, right?

Well, formally this Hall of Fame (HoF) is no more then a regularly updated
overview of the laptimes of a limited number of f1gp fans around the world.

But I like to see it as a simple, informative and, above all, @{b}fun@{ub} way
to compete with fellow Amiga Formula One Grand Prix fans. And beside that you
get all the info you need to (maybe? :) achieve the same standards and to keep
track of your rivals' moves.
All this is updated every two weeks, standings and rating information is added
and together with some bloke's random comments it is packaged as an easily
accessible AmigaGuide document.

You could follow the HoF passively, simply picking it up somewhere every two
weeks, but you could also become a member and enjoy several 'priviliges':
- you get your very own, very much unique player ID ! :-)
- you receive the HoF by E-Mail, straight from the source, automatically
  (notice that having E-Mail access is required to receive the HoF and/or
   to send in your times; snail-mail is barely an option...)
- you get to battle some unexpecting other members for real !
- you could even score points and see nothing in return for it ;-)
- you could try to talk some sense into me, whether it is about HoF matters
  or not...

Whatever you make of the above, just remember that the HoF is here for all
enthusiasts around, and that everybody gets a chance to hold eternal fame (or
to be forever lame ;).

Both the 'rules' and our common spirit should see to that. Fit yourself in!

@endnode

