@node "Rules" "The Rules!"

@{b}->  RULES!@{ub}

The rules have come to play a major role in the Amiga Hall of Fame.
With all the patches available, it is very important for players to have read 
@{b}and@{ub} understood what is about to follow.
Please note that the rules assume you to be familiar with Oliver Robert's F1GP
Editor V3.x, because this tool provides all the patches currently relevant and
the accompanying terminology. Refer to either Aminet or Oliver's homepage (see
@{"F1GP homepage" link "Address++" 0} for your copy (plug plug :-)


@{b}->  General rules@{ub}

_All_ members are expected to play fair, including the following presumptions.
'Options' allow for deviations from these standards. Players should @{u}always@{uu}
send in the options they used too! 

@{b}@{fg shine}o@{fg text}@{ub}   @{i}Qualifying@{ui} times (racing times theoretically are slower)
@{b}@{fg shine}o@{fg text}@{ub}   Q-compound tires
@{b}@{fg shine}o@{fg text}@{ub}   ACE-mode (=none of the driving aids)
@{b}@{fg shine}o@{fg text}@{ub}   Digital joystick
@{b}@{fg shine}o@{fg text}@{ub}   Reasonable style of driving:
    @{b}@{fg shine}o@{fg text}@{ub}   No cutting of  corners!
    @{b}@{fg shine}o@{fg text}@{ub}   No kamikaze actions on other cars, forcing your way through
    @{b}@{fg shine}o@{fg text}@{ub}   @{b}No slipstreaming!@{ub}

To prevent slipstreaming you could select all drivers and use only the first.
No car will get on the track then. If you decide to leave things as they are,
you are simply not allowed to send in any times you set with slipstreaming...
Simple, eh? ;)

Also it is not appreciated if you set your records by saving the game before
each corner and perfect that bit to the max. Although it's a very efficient
method, you @{b}must@{ub} set your records in one go! If you want to see where
you went wrong, use either 'Splittime' from Rene Smit, or AGPPerf from Grant
Reeve. Or both.
(btw: saving just before finishing your warmup lap @{i}is @{ui} allowed).

That's for general rules. But the patches are even more critical. Read on!


@{b}->  What's allowed and what's not@{ub}

A quick walkthrough of the V3 F1GP-Editor windows:
@{i} Find your latest copy of F1GP-Ed on either Aminet (game/misc dir) or on
the F1GP homepages (see @{"elsewhere" link "address++" 0} in the HoF) @{ui}
Due to the fast updating of most utilities, you may find some items moved
or under a different name. The general idea is still the same though.

@{i}FILE EDITORS @{ui}
@{b}@{fg shine}o@{fg text}@{ub}   @{b}Teams:@{ub} everything allowed, as it will only alter the behavior
    of computer cars, or other non-influential stuff.
@{b}@{fg shine}o@{fg text}@{ub}   @{b}Drivers@{ub}: same thing.
@{b}@{fg shine}o@{fg text}@{ub}   @{b}Car Setups:@{ub} Alter them all, or wait for the HoF to be released
    with data-files that do it for you! (Anybody interested? :)
@{b}@{fg shine}o@{fg text}@{ub}   @{b}Lap Records:@{ub} this is starting to get boring...
@{b}@{fg shine}o@{fg text}@{ub}   @{b}Camera Views:@{ub} I told you so...
@{b}@{fg shine}o@{fg text}@{ub}   @{b}Car Control:@{ub} If you use the twin button option, add the '2' option
@{b}@{fg shine}o@{fg text}@{ub}   @{b}Standard Options:@{ub} Remember that you should be racing at ACE level,
    so set the 'Opposition Standard' (race options) and the 'Help options'
    accordingly, or include the info with your times.
    'Game Options' are up to you.
@{b}@{fg shine}o@{fg text}@{ub}   @{b}In-Game Prefs@{ub}: If you're racing for the HoF, the 'Frames/sec should
    not be set higher than 10 fps. A pity for the owners of fast Amigas, but
    10 fps is sustainable on all Amiga models, and thus gives everybody an
    equal chance. (As you may have guessed: higher framerates influences the
    car's behaviour and consequentially allow you to set artificially fast
    times...
    In your spare time though, you can use whatever framerate you wish ;)
    'Car Fragility' should be kept standard, or set with the 199x datafile
    (which actually makes your car a bit more fragile).
@{b}@{fg shine}o@{fg text}@{ub}   @{b}Preferences:@{ub} All alterations allowed.
@{b}@{fg shine}o@{fg text}@{ub}   @{b}Cheats:@{ub} 'All Driving Aids' not allowed. If you still use them, make
            sure you turn everything off when you race for the HoF, or include
            the relevant 'options'
            'Q Tyres in Practice' and 'Unlimited Q Tyres' _are_ allowed.
            'Use Team HP' is @{b}not@{ub} allowed (unless the team's HP
            incidentally is 716 HP as well...but you better not use this option)
            'Degrade HP' is allowed :-) But you are advised (and allowed) to
            turn this off and have 716 HP available during every session.
            'Player HP' must absolutely be kept at 716. Always!
            'Finish HP' is irrelevant during qualifying sessions...

@{i}MEMORY PATCHES @{ui}
@{b}@{fg shine}o@{fg text}@{ub}   @{b}Car Control (Patch F1GP):@{ub} You are advised to install all routines and
            turn off traction control if you prefer that (only from v3.01 onward!)
    But, the 'snapshot keys' shouldn't be used at all.
@{b}@{fg shine}o@{fg text}@{ub}   @{b}Information (GP Patch):@{ub} fully legal. Stay away from the keys
    that alter game speed though (never know what could happen).
@{b}@{fg shine}o@{fg text}@{ub}   @{b}Local Speed Factors:@{ub} Legal too. Can reduce the amount of time computer
    cars are in your way, adding realism. (Remember: no slipstreaming!)

@{i}OTHER @{ui}
@{b}@{fg shine}o@{fg text}@{ub}   Can't find anything here that isn't legal...

@{b}->  'Miscellaneous' tools@{ub}

Other tools available include:
@{b}@{fg shine}o@{fg text}@{ub}   @{b}F1Ed@{ub} by Steve and Phil Smith. Similar to earlier versions of
    Oliver Robert's Editor. For similar parts similar rule limitations apply...
@{b}@{fg shine}o@{fg text}@{ub}   @{b}SplitTime@{ub} by Rene Smit. Fully legal and very useful. (Another plug?)
    Rene is constantly adding new features, but the latest version (that he
    wants to release) can be found on the F1GP homepages and Aminet.
@{b}@{fg shine}o@{fg text}@{ub}   @{b}AGPPerf@{ub} by Grant Reeve. Legal and amazing info on your performance.
    AGPPerf was released in October is certainly going to add to the scene.
    The latest version is available from Aminet and the F1GP homepages.

Questions about either Splittime or AGGPerf are best directed to the authors,
who are both listed somewhere among the members.

These rules have become quite a bit longer than I'd like'em to be..:-\
If you have any doubt, questions or serious problems with these rules, please
let me know!

@endnode

@node "layout" "Template for entries"

@{b}->  Template for entries@{ub}

When submitting laptimes, please try to use the following layout for it.
Stronger still: if you don't use the template, you're bound to see your
records back for correction. Cut this piece out and overtype it with your
own data! The header bit can be omitted. The name of the circuit should be
in the vicinity of the times you send in ;)

If you are unfamiliar with the HoF, this is also the place to read what info
this Hall of Fame can give you.

All of the tables conform to the following layout:

 TIME      ID  DATE     OPTS   [ F/R ]  F/R  [1,2,3,4,5,6]       Score
------------------------------------------------------------------------
*1:23.456  XY  dd-mm-yy        [32/32]  10R  [24,31,38,45,52,60] xx.xxx
  ^        ^    ^        ^        ^      ^         ^             ^
  |        |    |        |        |      |         |             Rated score
  |        |    |        |        |      |         Gear setup
  |        |    |        |        |      Break Balance Front or Rear
  |        |    |        |        Wingsetting Front/Rear respectively
  |        |    |        Non-rule options (see possible opts below)
  |        |    Date on which record was set or received
  |        Player-ID
  Self explanatory


@{b}->  POSSIBLE OPTIONS (opts)@{ub}

 Br   Auto Brakes              A    A-compound tires     Rxxx Race at xxx%
 G    Auto gears               B    B-compound
 Sp   Self-Righting Spins      C    C-compound            
 L    Best Line                D    D-compound
 S    Suggested gears          J    Analogue joystick    K    Used keyboard

 2    2 button gears           f5   @   10 fps PAL
 H    HP fixed at 716
 T    Traction control off

@endnode

